Copilot Prompt 1 — Django REST backend skeleton (minimal, ready for JWT)

What it does: creates a teedhub_backend Django project, installs/sets up DRF, CORS, SimpleJWT, and an /api/hello/ endpoint + JWT token endpoints.

Prompt (paste to Copilot):
Create a Django REST backend skeleton called teedhub_backend. Do the following automatically:

Create and activate a virtualenv (venv) and a requirements.txt with at least: django, djangorestframework, django-cors-headers, djangorestframework-simplejwt.

django-admin startproject teedhub_backend and inside it python manage.py startapp core.

Edit teedhub_backend/settings.py to:

add 'rest_framework', 'corsheaders', and 'core' to INSTALLED_APPS.

insert 'corsheaders.middleware.CorsMiddleware' at top of MIDDLEWARE.

set CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS = ["http://localhost:5173"].

add REST_FRAMEWORK = { "DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES": ("rest_framework_simplejwt.authentication.JWTAuthentication",) }

set USE_I18N = True and add LANGUAGES = [('en','English'), ('sw','Kiswahili')] and LOCALE_PATHS = [BASE_DIR / 'locale'].

Create core/views.py with a simple DRF view @api_view(['GET']) that returns {"message":"Welcome to TEED Hub API"}.

Edit teedhub_backend/urls.py to include:

path api/hello/ -> the hello view

SimpleJWT endpoints: api/token/ and api/token/refresh/

Output a README.md with exact commands to run: python -m venv venv, source venv/bin/activate (Windows note), pip install -r requirements.txt, python manage.py migrate, python manage.py runserver.

Add a short core/tests.py test that hits /api/hello/ and asserts the message.

Generate the files and full code blocks for each file. Keep the code minimal and clear.

